  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using the rest client with an invalid url example `http//localhost:8080` note the missing colon. Something makes the calls never return, and timeout values are also ignored. Using `@URL` from hibernate validator is a good way to catch it, but still I believe it should not hang.\r\n\r\nIn the reproducer I am using quartz scheduler as well. IN that case the app fully hangs and becomes totally unresponsive, it needs to be killed -9.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe invalid url should throw a runtime exception of something instead of making the app hang\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe full application hangs and is not stoppable without killing it\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nReproduder: https://github.com/manofthepeace/quarkus-reproducer-httpHang\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n1. mvn quarkus:dev\r\n2. app will hang you need to kill it.\r\n\r\nTo make it work;\r\n1. in the application.properties change `http//localhost:8080` to `http://localhost:8080`\r\n2. mvn quarkus:dev\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nDarwin Kernel Version 20.6.0\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment Temurin-17.0.2+8 (build 17.0.2+8\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.7.2\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\nApache Maven 3.8.4\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
